6:
Magnificent! Ocean, as far as the eye
can see.
9:
Yeah, it's pretty amazing. Try not to
get lost, Razelt.
13:
I am no addlepated gaffer! Now, I wish
to journey out onto the waves.
17:
Ahoy, sailors! I bestow upon you the
honor of my first sea voyage!
20:
What's that, lad? You lookin' to come
sailing?
22:
Yes. A prince of the Farlands shall grace
your decks.
25:
Well, if you can cough up the money,
who be a humble sailor to complain?
So, what kind of island's this Farlands
anyways?
28:
The Farlands is a great kingdom, and
I one of its leaders. When you address
me, it should be with honor and respect!
30:
A kingdom? Never heard of one. It have
somethin' to do with the Gaean
government?
31:
Anyways, give me a hand with this here
cargo. Then you can go struttin' and
crowin' on deck all you want.
36:
Does lineage mean nothing in different
worlds? I am beginning to feel... small...
40:
Yeah. I mean, respect's usually
something you have to earn. But at
least you're learning to stay out of
trouble. I'm so proud...
45: That is not how one talks to a prince!
50:
*sigh* But I will abandon my title for
now. While we are on this ship, I am
simply Razelt.
53:
Great. It's important to just be yourself
sometimes, you know?
59:
I do. I only wish my younger brother
did as well.
64:
You have a little brother?
Are you guys close?
67:
He is a gentle child—quite different
from you. Yet he holds a powerful
position in court, and is often pulled
into political affairs.
69:
As fourteenth in line to the throne,
I am largely left to my own devices.
But my brother cannot do as he wishes.
71:
I would share my freedom with him...
But perhaps it is not my place.
76:
He's family. You SHOULD be hanging out.
And I'm sure even a prince has time for
a fishing trip.
81: Yes. Perhaps we CAN go fishing...
86:
L-look alive, lads! We're bein' attacked
by pirates!
99:
Haah-hah-hah! Are you likin' this lovely
cannon we found? Just gotta
light 'er up, and she can turn any vessel
into splinters!
100:
Now, unless you want to be makin'
friends with the fishes, you best start
handin' over your cargo. Come on now!
No time for dilly-dallying!
106:
Wait, a cannon?! Razelt, think you can
take it?!
109:
I am Razelt of the House of Nialas!
I fear no cannon...
113:
A-and would stand my ground even
in the face of d-d-d-d-death!
118:
You're worrying me. Well, I... I might be
able to cut down the cannonball or...
124:
S-stay behind me, Alk.
I will keep you safe.
128:
Lad! You're shakin' like a leaf.
You best find somewhere to hide—
132:
A prince who trembles is still a prince!
And a lord who cannot lead on the
battlefield is not fit to lead at all!
136:
For honor and country, I call upon thee!
Ward thy people, Lord's Aegis!
141:
Hah-hah-hah! What are a few
cannonballs?! The real Lord's Aegis
could withstand a dragon's wrath!
144:
Wait, so that's not the real thing?
Well, whatever it is, it's getting the
job done!
148:
We are being boarded! Alk, fend
them off! My knees have given way!
153:
What?! You were just hurling attitude
at them! How are you still scared?!
159:
Three cheers for the hero who saved
our ship! Three cheers for Razelt from
the Farlands! Hip, hip, hooray!
162:
Nice work, hero. Bet you're the first
Nialas to be celebrated in a different
world.
165: Words must be backed by action.
169: And a prince must protect the people!
174: Guess I didn't have to worry after all.
178:
Hah-hah... hah?
What... did you mean by that?
186:
Then let us return! All of Starview
must hear of my valor!
194:
Haha! Of course! "The Tale of Prince
Razelt and His Loyal Servant, Alk..."
It has a nice ring to it.
199: Wait. Prince Razelt and his WHAT?!
